</P>
<P>
   American sports in the 20th century.
</P>
<P>
   12. THE ART OF HAPPINESS, by the Dalai Lama and Howard C.
</P>
<P>
   Cutler. (Riverhead, $22.95.) What Buddhism and common sense
</P>
<P>
   tell us about everyday problems.
</P>
<P>
   13. WE INTERRUPT THIS BROADCAST, by Joe Garner.
</P>
<P>
   (Sourcebooks, $45.) How radio and television reported
</P>
<P>
   historic events over the past 60 years.
</P>
<P>
   14. GALILEO'S DAUGHTER, by Dava Sobel. (Walker, $27.)
