<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Tops in my book
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Who are the greatest athletes from Georgia? The
Atlanta Journal-Constitution and Sports Illustrated published lists
of the people they chose. The Dec. 26 AJC named Henry Aaron, for
the most home runs in a career, and Bobby Jones, a Golf Grand Slam
winner in 1930, as the top two. The Dec. 27 Sports Illustrated
named its top two: Ty Cobb, who had baseball's best lifetime
batting average (.366), and Herschel Walker, a University of
Georgia football player who won the Heisman Trophy in 1982. Check
out the full lists at your library.
</P>
<P>
   PICK SI FOR KIDS' GREATEST ATHLETES
</P>
<P>
   You can vote for your favorite athletes at Sports Illustrated
for Kids' Web site at www.sikids.com. Categories include greatest
streaks, greatest feats, best athlete of the decade and another
important category: best nickname. While you're visiting the site,
check the Stanley Skunk comic. Stanley's a fragrant jock who just
wants to play ball. Plus, you can send skunk mail to friends and
neighbors!
</P>
<P>
   HAVE A HAPPY SCHOLARSHIP
</P>
<P>
   The next time you get a Happy Meal, be sure to check it
carefully _ it could pay for part of your college education.
McDonald's is offering four $25,000 scholarships during the next
year. Sure, your chances of winning are slim. But you've got to eat
anyway, so when you're at Mickey D's, be sure to look. Good luck!
</P>
