</P>
<P>
   &UR; 2006: &LR;  The moon's shadow will sweep over Egypt and run through
the Mediterranean.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; 2009: &LR;  The greatest, longest solar eclipse of the 21st century
will cross China and the Pacific Ocean, offering a rare 6.5 minutes
of daytime darkness.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; 2012: &LR;  Venus will transit the sun again, the last such event of
the century. This time it will be visible from North America.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; 2017: &LR;  Breaking a 38-year drought, a total eclipse of the sun
will slash the United States from coast to coast, briefly turning
