<HEADLINE>
A TOUGH TALE OF HITLER'S RISE 
</HEADLINE>
   (or use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``The Harmonists'' _ This overlooked story about
entertainers during the rise of Hitler didn't get the push it
needed during its theatrical release but it's a terrific find for
those looking for a neglected film at video stores. Highlighted by
fine performances and an unsentimental story, this mix of music and
history is touchingly tough.
</P>
<P>
   A VIDEO FOR PARENTS WHO WANT TO SLEEP LATE: If the kids are
already bored with their gifts, head to the video store and hope
that ``Gulliver's Travels'' is available. Paramount, whose
animation department was overshadowed by Disney, Warner Bros., and
MGM, was responsible for one of the greatest feature-length
animated films ever made _ Dave Fleischer's adaptation of Jonathan
Swift's classic. The DVD version is astounding _ bringing out all
the brilliance of the hand-painted cels and featuring a well-done
documentary on Fleisher and the painstaking restoration process.
For adults and children alike.
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Tuesday: ``The Thomas Crown Affair'' (DVD),
``Sayonara,'' ``Andy Kaufman Plays Carnegie Hall.'' Jan. 11: ``The
Art of Buster Keaton'' (DVD), ``The Big Brass Ring,'' ``The Lost
Man,'' ``Detroit Rock City,'' ``Mystery Men'' (DVD), ``The Extreme
Adventures of Super Dave.'' Jan. 18: ``Bowfinger'' (DVD), ``An
Ideal Husband,'' ``Twin Falls Idaho'' (DVD), ``The Hitchhiker,''
``From Dusk to Dawn 3,'' ``Bonanno: A Godfather's Story,'' ``Animal
Farm,'' ``The 13th Warrior,'' ``The Wood'' (DVD). Jan. 25:
``Runaway Bride''(DVD), ``My Life So Far,'' ``The Sex Monster,''
``My Son the Fanatic,'' ``Love Is in the Air,'' ``Conceiving Ada''
(DVD), ``The Tempest,'' ``Woman Wanted.'' Feb. 1: ``Love Stinks''
(DVD), ``The Winslow Boy'' (DVD), ``The Cabinet of Dr. Caligari,''
``Nosferatu.'' Feb. 8: ``Blue Streak'' (DVD), ``Fist of the
Legend,'' ``Absence of the Good'' (DVD), ``Ruby Bridges.'' Feb. 15:
``Breakfast of Champions,'' ``Big Fella'' (DVD), ``Song of
Freedom'' (DVD), ``In Too Deep,'' ``Daughters of the Dust,''
``Total Recall 2070,'' ``Entropy,'' ``Joe the King'' (DVD), ``The
Lovers on the Bridge.'' Feb. 22: ``Get Bruce!,'' ``Tail Lights
Fade'' (DVD), ``Galaxina.''
</P>
