<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ That battered lame duck, President
Clinton, was first out of the box in the new century with an agenda
for his last year in power while congressional Republicans are
still squabbling among themselves over what to do. They have lost
their way. Their tax-cut proposals don't sell, and they are out of
ideas. No wonder voters now tilt toward the Democrats in generic
congressional surveys. By MARIANNE MEANS.
