<HEADLINE>
BOOKS RECENTLY REVIEWED IN THE BOSTON GLOBE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 c.2000   The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Fortune's Rocks'' by Anita Shreve (Little, Brown, $24.95). A
page-turner about a girl who has a tragic affair with an older
man. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Anne Morrow Lindbergh'' by Susan Hertog (Nan A.
Talese/Doubleday, $30). In search of a living moral example, the
biographer finds a woman who married the century's dominant public
hero but who craved privacy and silence. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Flu'' by Gina Kolata (Farrar, Straus &AMP; Giroux, $25). A
masterly recounting of medical history, and a good mystery story
about the pandemic of 1918-19. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Yeats's Ghosts: The Secret Life of W. B. Yeats'' by Brenda
Maddox (HarperColl2). How the spirit world, and a spirited
woman, aided the great Irish poet.
</P>
