</P>
<P>
   TAIWAN-POLITICS (Hong Kong) _ In a proposal that could
foreshadow new rules for Taiwan's politics, the faltering
presidential candidate of the long-ruling Nationalist Party has
proposed that its vast business holdings be placed in a trust and
that the party end its direct role in managing hundreds of
companies in which it owns shares. By Erik Eckholm.
</P>
