it's such a great idea. By Randi Hutter Epstein. (700 words)
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-PATIENT-RIGHTS (Undated) _ Patients have a right to informed
consent, and they're entitled to make the decisions about their
lives, even if they make the wrong ones. Doctors often try to
direct, but only sometimes is their advice followed. By Sandeep
Jauhar, M.D. (1540 words)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-VITAL-SIGNS (Undated) _ News and notes on health and
fitness:
</P>
<P>
   _ Drivers who work night shifts or long hours (or who have more
than one job) are much more likely to be in a car accident caused
by being tired, a new study suggests. (275 words).
</P>
<P>
   _ Versatile vitamin C may also be effective in treating
moderately high blood pressure, the Pauling Institute reports. (250
words)
</P>
<P>
   _ Aware of many devastating effects, Michigan researchers plan
to explore the positive phenomena that occur in people who are
prisoners of war. (215 words)
</P>
<P>
   _ Patients seldom receive full and complete information from
their doctors, a medical journal concludes, but surgeons do a
better job than primary care doctors. (315 words)
</P>
<P>
   _ People with a history of depression do not necessarily have a
harder time of giving up smoking, but they may become more
depressed once the habit is broken. (185 words)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-Q&AMP;A (Undated) _ Science question answered: Is black ice
really black? What is it, exactly? By C. Claiborne Ray. (300 words)
