   CYBER-TERROR (Nashua, N.H.) _ The murder of Amy Boyer by a
stranger who posted his plans on a web site has drawn national
attention to the threat posed by cyber-terrorism. By Ellen Barry.
1380 words.
</P>
<P>
   MILLENNIUM-FACE (Undated) _ A constant question in Jamy Gaynor's
mind is what will her children look like. Will they take the strong
cheekbones and cocoa brown skin from her father's West Indian
heritage or the hazel eyes and lean stature from her mother's
English and slavic stock? The Gaynors are, demographers say, the
face of the next millenium, when the racial distinctions that have
defined American society for centuries will melt away. By Tatsha
Roberts. 1190 words.
</P>
