<P>
   SCI-ARMAGEDDON (Undated) _ The site of Revelation's Armageddon
may in fact be Megiddo, some scholars speculate. And what's being
dug up there now is casting some doubt on the Bible as a reliable
history of King David and Solomon the Wise. By John Noble Wilford.
(1775 words)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-STORM-FORECAST (Paris) _ The storms that devastated France
last week were not unprecedented. But because they came in ``like a
cannon shot'' across the Atlantic, where weather monitoring
stations are sparse, computer models failed to predict how intense
they would be. By Suzanne Daley. (1000 words)
</P>
