<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   SUGAR BOWL ADVANCE COVERAGE
</P>
<P>
   FBC-BOWDEN _ NEW ORLEANS _ It's been quite a year for Florida
State coach Bobby Bowden. In November, he became only the fifth
Division I coach in history to win 300 games. Bowden beat his son,
Clemson's Tommy Bowden, to do it. Now the 70-year-old coach has a
chance to reach another milestone by winning his second national
championship and posting the first perfect season in this, his 34th
year as a head coach. A lot of guys have won one national
championship, but only a handful have won two or more. Bowden would
love to join that group. ``It (winning two national titles) sort of
puts you at another level,'' said Bowden. ``I'd like that.'' This
will be the third time in the past four seasons that Bowden has
played for the national title. (Barnhart, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-SUGAR-MATCHUPS _ NEW ORLEANS _ Sugar Bowl matchups: Rushing
offense; passing offense; rushing defense; passing defense; special
teams; coaching; intangibles; prediction. (Barnhart, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   OTHER COLLEGE FOOTBALL NEWS
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FIESTA-FOLO _ TEMPE, Ariz. _ Folo story from Nebraska's
31-21 Fiesta Bowl victory over Tennessee. (Wilkinson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL/PROS
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PLAYOFF-ANALYSIS _ An Analysis: Now that the brackets are
set, we look at the teams that have the easiest route to the Super
Bowl. (Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-COACHING-CHANGES _ Green Bay coach Ray Rhodes was fired late
Sunday night; Pete Carroll was fired Monday morning; Bill Parcells
quit. (Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-COWBOYS _ AUSTYIN, Texas _The Dallas Cowboys are in the
playoffs. One day after grabbing the final postseason NFL spot with
a win over the New York Giants, the Cowboys turn their attention to
Minnesota. The Vikings whipped the Cowboys earlier this season but
had to rally from a big halftime deficit to do so. Developing.
(Rick Cantu, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   BASKTBALL/COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   BKN-ACC-SEC _ Most of the non-league games are over and it is
time to get down to business in ACC and SEC men's basketball. The
ACC, which begins league play Tuesday, has not been its usual
dominant self, while the SEC has been more successful. The SEC
schedule starts Wednesday. (Arey, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
16.
</P>
<P>
   BASKETBALL/PROS
</P>
<P>
   BKN-RIDER-RETURNS _ The Hawks' Isaiah Rider is scheduled to
return from his one-game suspension for Tuesday night's game at
Milwaukee. (Denberg, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 16.
</P>
<P>
   ROSNER-ROBINSON _AUSTIN, Texas _David Robinson is on schedule,
more or less, and that makes the San Antonio Spurs worth inspection
during the next few weeks. Robinson averaged 23.5 points in his
last two games _ 10 more than he had been scoring _ providing
assistance desperately needed by teammate Tim Duncan. Robinson also
grabbed 27 rebounds in the two games. Skeptics suggest Robinson's
performances were indicative of little except the caliber of
competition _ Golden State and Vancouver, each so inept that its
coaches were recently fired. Robinson has bigger obstacles in front
of him. San Antonio faces Minnesota tonight, Seattle on Wednesday,
Phoenix, Orlando and Utah after that, opponents that will prove
whether the Spurs' 21-10 record was inflated by the likes of Golden
State and Vancouver. (Rosner, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
