of the juggling profession. Even rarer, she juggles clubs, which
are heftier than the batons, rings or soft balls that other female
jugglers favor. ``You can train and train, but if you miss one
thing, juggling becomes an ungrateful profession,'' she says.
(Ozier Muhammad/The New York Times)
