Five-foot-four and 110 pounds, Natalia Sarygina appears to have
more grace than intensity. At 28, she is among a handful of women
worldwide at the top of her profession: juggling. It is a field in
which men outnumber women 9 to 1, according to the International
Juggling Association. ``I think man is a man, he's more strong,''
she shrugs, speaking in Russian-laced English. ``A woman? It's a
woman.'' (Ozier Muhammad/The New York Times) LITE
