Fernando Botero. ``Botero is a very important part of our cultural
identity, so of course we have always wanted him here,'' says Ms.
Moreno. ``He may live in Italy, but he has never stopped being from
Antioquia for a single day of his life, so that his work has always
portrayed us and who we are.'' (Larry Rohter/The New York Times)
