Moran-Wollens, 13, working out with her personal trainer, Rodica
Vranceanu at Radu Gym in Manhattan. Even children now are turning
to personal trainers, and at least some exercise experts don't
think it's such a great idea. (Chester Higgins Jr./The New York
Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT6) WASHINGTON -- Jan. 03, 2000 -- SCI-FOSSIL-EROSION-2 --
The stegosaur displayed at the National Museum of Natural History
in Washington, savaged for years by the hot breath of museum
visitors, is now, like some of its fossil neighbors, threatened
with destruction. The museum, part of the Smithsonian Institution,
hopes to save its most endangered fossils by removing them from
display and exhibiting only their plastic casts. (Marty Katz/The
New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) WASHINGTON -- Jan. 03, 2000 -- SCI-FOSSIL-EROSION-1 --
This triceratops at the Smithsonian's National Museum of Natural
History will be replaced by a cast, but the skull will stay. The
biggest factor in the deterioration pf such prized fossils is
pyrite disease, a condition hastened by moisture, in which sulfur
and iron combine as pyrite (fool's gold), which replaces and
greatly weakens the mineralized bone in fossils. (Marty Katz/The
New York Times) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT4) NEW YORK -- Jan. 03, 2000 -- SCI-MOUTH-BACTERIA -- A
study last month in The Proceedings of the National Academy of
Sciences identified 37 new kinds of bacteria thriving between teeth
and gum. The research brings the total known species of oral
wildlife to about 500, some of which are permanent residents while
others may just be passing through. (Chester Higgins Jr./The New
York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. -- Jan. 03, 2000 -- FBN-JETS-PARCELS-3 --
Bill Parcells announces his resignation as head coach of the New
York Jets on Monday. Parcells resigned after three seasons as coach
of the New York Jets, but will remain with the team as its chief
operating officer. (Barton Silverman/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. -- Jan. 03, 2000 --
FBN-JETS-PARCELS-2 -- Bill Parcells, head coach of the New York
Jets, during his team's game against the Seattle Seahawks on Sunday
at Giants Stadium. The Jets won 19-9. Parcells resigned on Monday
after three seasons as coach of the New York Jets, but will remain
with the team as chief operating officer. (Ozier Muhammad/The New
York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) TAMPA, Fla. -- Jan. 03, 2000 -- FBN-JETS-PARCELS -- Bill
Parcells, then coach of the New York Giants, is carried of the
field by his team after he led them to a 20-19 victory over the
Buffalo Bills in Super Bowl XXV in 1991. Parcells resigned on
Monday after three seasons as coach of the New York Jets, but will
remain with the team as chief operating officer. Parcells turned
around three franchises in his history as a coach. He won two Super
Bowls with the Giants and got to one with the Patriots. He was 9-7,
12-4 and 8-8 as Jets coach. (Vic DeLucia/The New York Times)
</P>
