   At issue are such matters as how to structure security
guarantees _ possibly using United Nations and U.S. peacekeeping
troops _ for Israel; a timetable for Israeli withdrawal from the
strategic Golan Heights; how to allocate precious fresh water
supplies from the Sea of Galilee, in the Golan; and how to set up
the first-ever commercial and diplomatic ties between Israel and a
country that has been its avowed foe since the birth of the Jewish
state in 1948.
</P>
<P>
   Israeli troops seized the Golan territories from Syria during
the 1967 war, after Syria joined Egypt and Jordan in attacking
Israel.
</P>
<P>
   Absent from the talks here was Syria's aging President Hafez
al-Assad, who is reported to be in uncertain health.
</P>
<P>
   Rubin said U.S. officials are confident that Sharaa is
negotiating with Assad's full confidence and authority, however,
Assad's personal attention is likely to be required to seal any
comprehensive accord.
</P>
<P>
   ``We do expect him to be involved,'' Rubin said, though it was
too soon to say whether Assad would make an appearance in
Shepherdstown.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
